U.K. Oil, Gas Industry Employs 440,000, Meets 90% of Oil Demand

-- B y   T i m   F a r r a n d
-- 
2011-10-11T09:12:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/u-k-oil-gas-industry-employs-440-000-meets-90-of-oil-demand.html
The U.K. oil and gas industry
employs about 440,000 people with production valued at 32
billion pounds in 2010, according to a report by industry body
Oil & Gas U.K.  The report shows that more than 40 billion barrels of oil
and gas equivalent have been extracted from the U.K. continental
shelf as a result of 468 billion pounds of investment over the
past 40 years.  The U.K. produced an average 2.2 million barrels of oil and
gas per day in 2010, meeting about 90 percent of the countryâ€™s
oil demand and 60 percent of its need for gas, Oil & Gas U.K.
said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
